    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-24T23:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-24T23:35:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.42/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-25T08:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 25, 1941—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>237. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 117 of October 17, 11 p.m.<note
                        n="58" xml:id="d353fn58">Not printed.</note> The Minister of Education
                    informs me that the Council <pb facs="0389" n="381" xml:id="pg_381"/> of
                    Ministers has now authorized him to extend an official invitation to American
                    educators to come to Iran to make an educational survey.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
